`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The achievement system was decomposed in US-127 (core.ts + world.ts + checker.ts + types.ts) to satisfy the 300-line file limit. The test file imports from `"./achievements"` which TypeScript automatically resolves to the directory's `index.ts` barrel — no path changes needed in tests.
- `checkAchievements` is a pure function (stats + alreadyEarned[] → newlyEarned[]) — zero store/ECS dependencies, making it trivially testable with plain objects.
- The "no double-trigger" test pattern (`checkAchievements(stats, ["first-seed"])` → not contain `"first-seed"`) is the key idempotency guard.
